                         1     ;Write a program to display the remaining time in three digits using three sevensegment displays.
                         2     ;For example, if the ;remaining time is currently 20.1 minutes, then
                         3     ;we would be displaying 201 on the three seven segment displays. We would then
                         4     ;observe 201, 200, 199, â€¦ , 001, 000. You need to write the delay subroutine in such a
                         5     ;way that when the program is simulated, the time display should be updated at every
                         6     ;0.1 min approximately. Note that the actual 8051 delays and the delays one would
                         7     ;get when simulations are performed, may be quite different. Remaining time
                         8     ;initialization will be done within the code (largest value 99.9 minutes). When the
                         9     ;remaining time hits zero, display blinking characters of your own design.
